abstract: Bernie Sanders says he doesn't plan to divulge additional information about his health, months after suffering a heart attack on the campaign trail and subsequently pledging to release “comprehensive” medical records.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders says he doesn't plan to divulge additional information about his health, months after suffering a heart attack on the campaign trail and subsequently pledging to release “comprehensive” medical records.
headline_main: Questions About Sanders' Health Linger After Heart Attack
headline_print_headline: Questions About Sanders' Health Linger After Heart Attack

abstract: Florida cannot bar felons from voting over unpaid fines and fees related to their convictions, a federal appeals court ruled on Wednesday, opening the door to a potential surge in the number of eligible voters in the battleground state ahead of November 2020's  presidential election.
snippet: Florida cannot bar felons from voting over unpaid fines and fees related to their convictions, a federal appeals court ruled on Wednesday, opening the door to a potential surge in the number of eligible voters in the battleground state ahead of No...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Florida cannot bar felons from voting over unpaid fines and fees related to their convictions, a federal appeals court ruled on Wednesday, opening the door to a potential surge in the number of eligible voters in the battleground state ahead of November 2020's presidential election.
headline_main: U.S. Appeals Court Rules Florida Cannot Bar Felons From Voting Over Unpaid Fees
headline_print_headline: U.S. Appeals Court Rules Florida Cannot Bar Felons From Voting Over Unpaid Fees

abstract: Family members of six American oil executives jailed in Venezuela are accusing Nicolas Maduro’s government of “forced disappearance” after the men were inexplicably missing for the scheduled start of their trial on Wednesday.
snippet: Family members of six American oil executives jailed in Venezuela are accusing Nicolas Maduro’s government of “forced disappearance” after the men were inexplicably missing for the scheduled start of their trial on Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — Family members of six American oil executives jailed in Venezuela are accusing Nicolas Maduro’s government of “forced disappearance” after the men were inexplicably missing for the scheduled start of their trial on Wednesday.
headline_main: Maduro Accused of 'Disappearing' US Oilmen as Trial Delayed
headline_print_headline: Maduro Accused of 'Disappearing' US Oilmen as Trial Delayed

abstract: A federal judge on Thursday is scheduled to sentence Roger Stone, a long-time adviser to U.S. President Donald Trump, in a criminal case that has roiled the Justice Department and drawn the Republican president's ire.

headline_main: Explainer: Who Is Roger Stone and Why Does He Face Prison?

abstract: Supporters of Senator Amy Klobuchar have also formed a super PAC. Both groups are now airing ads in Nevada.
snippet: Supporters of Senator Amy Klobuchar have also formed a super PAC. Both groups are now airing ads in Nevada.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Supporters of Senator Elizabeth Warren have formed a last-minute super PAC to boost her candidacy in Nevada and are plunging $1 million into television and other ads in the race’s final days, despite the Massachusetts senator’s previous outspoken opposition to such groups.

abstract: Rod Blagojevich, a former Illinois governor forced out of office for trying to peddle Barack Obama's vacated U.S. Senate seat, thanked President Donald Trump on Wednesday for commuting his prison sentence and again proclaimed his innocence.
snippet: Rod Blagojevich, a former Illinois governor forced out of office for trying to peddle Barack Obama's vacated U.S. Senate seat, thanked President Donald Trump on Wednesday for commuting his prison sentence and again proclaimed his innocence.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Rod Blagojevich, a former Illinois governor forced out of office for trying to peddle Barack Obama's vacated U.S. Senate seat, thanked President Donald Trump on Wednesday for commuting his prison sentence and again proclaimed his innocence.
headline_main: Former Illinois Governor Blagojevich Thanks Trump for Commuting Sentence
headline_print_headline: Former Illinois Governor Blagojevich Thanks Trump for Commuting Sentence

abstract: In a billionaire-to-billionaire media matchup, Tom Steyer is taking on Mike Bloomberg in a multimillion-dollar Super Tuesday ad buy, accusing the former New York City mayor of “racist” policies including “redlining” and the controversial “stop-and-frisk” tactic.

lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — In a billionaire-to-billionaire media matchup, Tom Steyer is taking on Mike Bloomberg in a multimillion-dollar Super Tuesday ad buy, accusing the former New York City mayor of “racist” policies including “redlining” and the controversial “stop-and-frisk” tactic.
headline_main: Steyer Cites 'Racist' Bloomberg Tactics in Super Tuesday Ad
headline_print_headline: Steyer Cites 'Racist' Bloomberg Tactics in Super Tuesday Ad
